explained in the description section.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Use <strong>Path.GetFullPath()</strong> method (built-in path canonicalization) in order to validate your <strong>absolute</strong> path and compare it with the requested path (</span></span>proceed<span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"> <strong>only</strong> if the both paths are equal) This method can be found in System.IO namespace.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Applying proper authorization.</span></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Use <strong>getCanonicalPath() </strong>method (built-in path canonicalization) and compare it with </span></span><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><strong>getAbsolutePath()</strong></span> method <span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">in order to validate your path <em>java.io.File</em> class.</span></span></li>\n\t<li><span style=\"font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\">Applying proper
